\p
\v 18 Don't let any of you fool yourselves. If anyoneВҰ114166 of you thinks they're wise by \add worldly standards\add*, then let \add those people\add* become вҖҳfoolishВҰ114176вҖҷ so that they really can become wise
\v 19 because this world'sВҰ114185 wisdomВҰ114183 is foolishnessВҰ114187 with \nd GodВҰ114190\nd*, because as it's writtenВҰ114192: вҖҳHe catchesВҰ114195 out the wise in theirВҰ114201 craftinessВҰ114200.вҖҷ\x + \xo 3:19: \xt Yob 5:13.\x*
\v 20 And furtherВҰ114203: вҖҳ\nd YahwehВҰ114204\nd* knows that the thoughts of wise people are uselessВҰ114213.вҖҷ\x + \xo 3:20: \xt Psa 94:11.\x*
\v 21 So then, don't let anyoneВҰ114215 boastВҰ114216 about peopleВҰ114218, becauseВҰ114220 everything \add already\add* belongs to all of youВҰ114221.
\v 22 \add Don't boast about\add* PaulВҰ114224 or ApollosВҰ114226 or CephasВҰ114228, or the worldВҰ114230 or lifeВҰ114232 or deathВҰ114234, or the presentВҰ114236 or the future. All of them belong to youВҰ114241,
\v 23 and youВҰ114244 belong to Messiah, and Messiah belongs to \nd GodВҰ114249\nd*.
\c 4
\s1 Status of the missionaries
\rem /s1 Paul and the Corinthians; The Ministry of the Apostles; Apostles of Christ
\p
\v 1 So then, people shouldВҰ114252 regard us as servants of \nd MessiahВҰ114256\nd* andВҰ114257 as stewards of God's mysteriesВҰ114259.
\v 2 What's more, stewards are expected to be trustworthy.
\v 3 But itВҰ114278 makes virtually no difference to me whether I'm being judged by youВҰ114282 all, or by a humanВҰ114286 court, because I don't even judge myselfВҰ114290.
\v 4 \add Yes,\add* my conscience is clear, but that won'tВҰ114297 mean that I'm declared вҖҳnot guiltyвҖҷ, becauseВҰ114293 it's \nd YahwehВҰ114306\nd* who'll be examiningВҰ114304 me.
\v 5 So don'tВҰ114309 make judgements ahead of time, butВҰ114326 wait untilВҰ114314 the \nd masterВҰ114318\nd* comesвҖ”the one who'll bring to light what's hiddenВҰ114323 in the darknessВҰ114325, and who will expose people's \add true\add* motives. At that time, \nd GodВҰ114340\nd* will praiseВҰ114335 each person \add who's acted faithfully\add*.
\p
\v 6 Now brothersВҰ114343 and sistersВҰ114343, I applied theseВҰ114341 things to myselfВҰ114346 and ApollosВҰ114348 for yourВҰ114350 sakes, so that through us you all might learnВҰ114355 this: вҖҳNot beyondВҰ114358 what is writtenВҰ114361,вҖҷ so that no one would be puffed up in favour of one againstВҰ114370 the otherВҰ114372,
\v 7 becauseВҰ114374 who makes you better than others? What do you have thatВҰ114380 wasn't given to you? And if it was given to you, why would you boastВҰ114388 as if it hadn't been given to you?
\p
\v 8 Are you all full already? Have you all already become rich? You think you're kings already, and don't need usвҖ”I wish you all were really reigning as kings, so we could reign with you,
\v 9 because it seems that God has exhibited us missionaries last \add of all\add*, as if sentencedВҰ114420 to deathВҰ114420вҖ”because weВҰ114423 have becomeВҰ114423 a spectacle to the worldВҰ114425вҖ”both to \add God's\add* messengersВҰ114427 andВҰ114428 to men.
\v 10 We \add appear as\add* fools for Messiah's sake, but you all are wise in Messiah. We are weak, but you all are strongВҰ114443. You all are honoured, but we are dishonouredВҰ114448.
\v 11 Right up to the present time, we're hungry and thirstyВҰ114456, we're poorlyВҰ114458 clothedВҰ114458 and brutally beatenВҰ114460, and we're homeless
\v 12 and working hardвҖ”working with our own handsВҰ114468. When people curse us, we blessВҰ114470 \add them\add*, and when they persecuteВҰ114471 us, we put up with it.\x + \xo 4:12: \xt Acts 18:3.\x*
\v 13 When people slander us, we answer gently. We've becomeВҰ114480 like the scum of the world, the world's trash, even untilВҰ114483 now.
\rem /s1 Fatherly Admonition
\p
\v 14 I'm not writingВҰ114488 this to shame you all, but to correct you as if you were myВҰ114493 \add own\add* dear childrenВҰ114492,
\v 15 because if you all would have thousandsВҰ114500 of guardians in Messiah, yet you wouldn't have many вҖҳfathersВҰ114508вҖҷ, because I fathered you in Messiah \nd Yeshua\nd* by means of the goodВҰ114515 messageВҰ114515.
\v 16 That's why I urge youВҰ114521 all to imitateВҰ114522 me,\x + \xo 4:16: \xt 1Cor 11:1; Php 3:17.\x*
\v 17 and that's why I sentВҰ114528 TimothyВҰ114530 to \add visit\add* you. He's like my own dear son in \nd YahwehВҰ114540\nd*, and he'll remindВҰ114543 you all about my waysВҰ114545 in \nd MessiahВҰ114549 Yeshua\nd*, just like I teachВҰ114556 everywhere in every church.
\p
\v 18 \add Now\add* some of you have become arrogantВҰ114564, as if I'm not able to come back to see you all,
\v 19 but if the \nd masterВҰ114573\nd* allows it, I'll come andВҰ114575 visit youВҰ114570 all again soon. Then I won'tВҰ114577 just see what any puffed-up people are \em saying\em*, but I'll also see what \em powerВҰ114584\em* they have,
\v 20 becauseВҰ114586 God's kingdomВҰ114590 isn'tВҰ114585 just mere words, butВҰ114593 it's \add a demonstration of\add* powerВҰ114595.
\v 21 What would you all prefer: should I come to you all with a rod, or \add come\add* with love and a gentleВҰ114609 spiritВҰ114606?
\c 5
\s1 Expelling the sexually immoral
\rem /s1 Expel the Immoral Brother!; Paul Condemns Spiritual Pride; Sexual Immorality Defiles the Church; Immorality in the Church
\p
\v 1 ActuallyВҰ114610, we've been hearing that there's sexual immorality there among youВҰ114614 all, andВҰ114616 so bad that even non-believers don'tВҰ114620 do it: a man is sleeping with his step-mother!\x + \xo 5:1: \xt Deu 22:30.\x*
\v 2 ThenВҰ114632 instead of being upset, you all \add seem\add* proud of it. This man should have been expelled out of yourВҰ114645 \add group\add*,
\v 3 because even though I'm not there physically, I am present in the spiritВҰ114662, and I've alreadyВҰ114663 made my judgementВҰ114664 about the man who's doing this, as if I were present.
\v 4 When you assemble togetherВҰ114679 in the name of ourВҰ114676 master Yeshua, my spiritВҰ114684 \add is there\add* along with the master \nd Yeshua's\nd* powerВҰ114687,
\v 5 \add then you should\add* hand this man over to SatanВҰ114698 to \add punish\add* his bodyВҰ114702, so that his spiritВҰ114705 can be savedВҰ114706 for when the \nd masterВҰ114711\nd* \add returns\add*.
\p
\v 6 It isn't goodВҰ114716 how you all boastВҰ114718. Don't you realise that a littleВҰ114723 bit of yeast can raise a whole loaf \add of bread\add*?\x + \xo 5:6: \xt Gal 5:9.\x*
\v 7 Get rid of the old yeast so that you'll all become fresh dough, just as you are unleavenedВҰ114740 bread. BecauseВҰ114742 \nd MessiahВҰ114749\nd*, ourВҰ114745 Passover lamb, has also been sacrificedВҰ114748\x + \xo 5:7: \xt Exo 12:5.\x*
\v 8 so that weВҰ114751 can be feastingВҰ114751, not with old yeast or with yeast of evil and wickednessВҰ114763, butВҰ114762 with unleavenedВҰ114766 breadВҰ114766 of sincerityВҰ114767 and of truthВҰ114769.\x + \xo 5:8: \xt Exo 13:7; Deu 16:3.\x*
\rem /s1 Sexual Immorality Must Be Judged
\p
\v 9 I wroteВҰ114770 to youВҰ114771 in my letterВҰ114774 not to associateВҰ114776 with sexuallyВҰ114777 immoralВҰ114777 people,
\v 10 \add butВҰ114790\add* certainlyВҰ114780 not \add meaning\add* worldly people who are sexuallyВҰ114782 immoralВҰ114782 or swindlersВҰ114792 or idolatersВҰ114794, becauseВҰ114795 \add that would mean that\add* you'd all have to leave this world.
\v 11 \add No,\add* I'm writing to tell youВҰ114807 all not to associateВҰ114809 with any so-called believer who's sexuallyВҰ114815 immoralВҰ114815 or greedy or an idolaterВҰ114820 or verbally abusive or a drunkardВҰ114825 or a swindlerВҰ114827. Don't even have a meal with such a person.
\p
\v 12 Why would it be my \add job\add* to judge outsidersВҰ114838вҖ”\add no,\add* shouldn't it be those \em insideВҰ114843\em* \add the assemblies\add* that you judge?
\v 13 \nd GodВҰ114854\nd* will judge the outsidersВҰ114852, \add butВҰ114850\add*:\x + \xo 5:13: \xt Deu 13:5; 17:7 (LXX).\x* вҖҳExpelВҰ114858 evilВҰ114862 \add people\add* from among yourselvesВҰ114865.вҖҷ
\c 6
\s1 Lawsuits among believers
\rem /s1 Lawsuits against Fellow Christians; Lawsuits among Christians; Avoiding Lawsuits with Christians
\p
\v 1 If anyoneВҰ114867 among youВҰ114869 all has a case againstВҰ114872 anotherВҰ114874 \add believer\add*, how dare they go to \add a secular\add* court in front of an unbelieving judgeВҰ114875 instead of to believers.
\v 2 Don't you realise that \add in the future\add*, believers will judge the world, andВҰ114893 if the world's going to be judgedВҰ114897 by all of you, surely you're competent enough \add now\add* to judge smaller cases?
\v 3 Don't youВҰ114905 realise that we'll judge \add God's\add* messengersВҰ114907? So surely we can judge things of \add this\add* life?
\v 4 \add So then,\add* if you have legal disputes about things of this life, why do you appoint people with no standing in the assemblyВҰ114922 as judges?
\v 5 I say \add that\add* to your shameВҰ114926. Don't you have anyoneВҰ114936 among you all who can arbitrate between believers?
\v 6 ButВҰ114954 instead, one believer goes to court against another, andВҰ114954 it's in front of unbelieversВҰ114958!
\p
\v 7 Actually, you're all disgraced already for havingВҰ114970 lawsuitsВҰ114968 among yourselvesВҰ114972. Why not rather be wrongedВҰ114977? Why not rather be cheated?
\v 8 ButВҰ114988 you're all wrongingВҰ114987 and cheating \add others, including\add* fellowВҰ114993 believersВҰ114993.
\rem /s1 Avoiding Sexual Sin
\p
\v 9 Or don'tВҰ114995 youВҰ114996 all know that \add вүҲthose who disobey\add* \nd GodВҰ115001\nd* won'tВҰ114995 inheritВҰ115004 his kingdomВҰ115002? Don't let yourselves be deceivedВҰ115006: those who are sexuallyВҰ115008 immoralВҰ115008 or idolatersВҰ115010, or adulterersВҰ115012 or male prostitutes or homosexuals,
\v 10 or thievesВҰ115019 or greedy, or drunkardsВҰ115028 or slanderers or swindlersВҰ115032, will inheritВҰ115036 God's kingdomВҰ115033.
\v 11 Now some of you all were like that, butВҰ115037 now you've been washedВҰ115042 and declared guiltless, and been declared innocent by the authority of the \nd masterВҰ115051 Yeshua MessiahВҰ115054\nd*, and by ourВҰ115061 god's \nd spiritВҰ115058\nd*.
\s1 Avoid sexual immorality
\rem /s1 Glorify God in Body and Spirit; Use Your Bodies for God's Glory
\p
\v 12 Some might say, вҖҳEverything is permissible for me,вҖҷ but not everything is beneficialВҰ115068. Everything might be permissible for me, but I don'tВҰ115066 want those things to have control over me.\x + \xo 6:12: \xt 1Cor 10:23.\x*
\v 13 You might say, вҖҳFood is for the stomach, and the stomach for food,вҖҷ but \nd GodВҰ115089\nd* will \add eventually\add* abolish them both. Also, the body is not \add meant to be used\add* for sexualВҰ115100 immoralityВҰ115100, but rather, for the master, and the master for the body.
\v 14 \add Actually,\add* \nd GodВҰ115111\nd* made the \nd masterВҰ115114\nd* come alive again, andВҰ115116 by hisВҰ115124 powerВҰ115123, he'll also do that for us.
\p
\v 15 Surely you all know that your bodiesВҰ115129 are parts of messiah's \add body\add*? Because of that, you shouldn't take your body back and then join it to a prostitute'sВҰ115143 \add body\add*. May it never happen!
\v 16 Or don'tВҰ115148 youВҰ115149 know that having sex with a prostituteВҰ115154 is a joining togetherВҰ115152, becauseВҰ115159 it says:\x + \xo 6:16: \xt Gen 2:24.\x* вҖҳThe twoВҰ115162 will become one bodyВҰ115156.вҖҷ
\v 17 But a person joining with the \nd masterВҰ115170\nd*, becomes one spiritВҰ115172 \add with him\add*.
\p
\v 18 \add Don't just walk away\add* from sexual immorality, but \em run away\em* from it, because other forms of disobeying God are outsideВҰ115183 the body, but sexual immorality is a sin againstВҰ115190 your own body.
\v 19 Surely you all know that yourВҰ115203 bodyВҰ115201 is a templeВҰ115204 of the holy \nd spiritВҰ115209\nd* who comes from \nd GodВҰ115215\nd* andВҰ115216 \add lives\add* within you.\x + \xo 6:19: \xt 1Cor 3:16; 2Cor 6:16.\x* No, you don'tВҰ115196 \add actually\add* own yourselvesВҰ115220
\v 20 becauseВҰ115222 a priceВҰ115223 was paid to buy you, so honourВҰ115224 \nd GodВҰ115227\nd* with yourВҰ115231 bodies.
\c 7
\s1 Advice concerning marriage
\rem /s1 Directions concerning Marriage; Instruction on Marriage; Sex, marriage, and divorce; Questions about Marriage
\p
\v 1 Now concerningВҰ115241 what you all wroteВҰ115244 \add to me\add*: вҖңIt's good for a man not to touchВҰ115250 a womanВҰ115248.вҖқ
\v 2 However, becauseВҰ115251 there is so much sexualВҰ115254 immoralityВҰ115254, each man shouldВҰ115259 have his own wife, and each womanВҰ115261 her own husbandВҰ115264.
\v 3 Both husbands and wives have a marital duty to each other \add in terms of sexual needsВҰ115274\add*:
\v 4 wives' bodies belong to their husbands, not to themselves, and similarly, husbands' bodies belong to their wives, not to themselves.
\v 5 Don't deprive each other, except by mutual agreement so that you may devote yourselves to prayerВҰ115321 for an agreed timeВҰ115314, and then be together againВҰ115323, so that SatanВҰ115335 can'tВҰ115309 \add easily\add* temptВҰ115332 you all becauseВҰ115336 of yourВҰ115339 lack of self-control.
\p
\v 6 But that isn'tВҰ115345 a commandВҰ115347вҖ”I'm only suggesting that it's good to do,\f + \fr 7:6 \ft It's not clear here whether Paul is referring back to marriage here (v2), or to abstaining from sex to focus on praying (v5).\f*
\v 7 and I wish everyoneВҰ115352 could be like me. ButВҰ115349 each person has their own gift from \nd GodВҰ115364\nd*вҖ”one has such-and-such a gift while someone else has a different one.
\p
\v 8 Now to the unmarriedВҰ115376 andВҰ115377 to the widowsВҰ115379 I say that it's goodВҰ115381 if theyВҰ115387 remainВҰ115387 like me,\f + \fr 7:8 \ft This is intentionally left ambiguous because we can't be certain what Paul meant here.\f*
\v 9 butВҰ115393 if they don'tВҰ115394 have self-control, they shouldВҰ115396 marry becauseВҰ115398 it's betterВҰ115397 to marry than to burn \add with sexual desire\add*.
\p
\v 10 Now I (\add well,\add* not I, butВҰ115410 the \nd masterВҰ115412\nd*) commandВҰ115407 marriedВҰ115406 people that a wifeВҰ115413 is not to be separatedВҰ115417 from her husbandВҰ115415\x + \xo 7:10-11: \xt Mat 5:32; 19:9; Mrk 10:11-12; Luk 16:18.\x*
\v 11 (butВҰ115421 even if she might be separatedВҰ115423, let her remainВҰ115424 unmarriedВҰ115425, or let her be reconciledВҰ115429 to the husband), and a husband is not to divorce a wife.
\p
\v 12 ButВҰ115450 to the rest I say (I, not the \nd masterВҰ115443\nd*) that if any believing husband has an unbelievingВҰ115449 wifeВҰ115447 and she agrees to live with him, he shouldn'tВҰ115441 divorce her.
\v 13 Similarly, if any womanВҰ115461 has an unbelievingВҰ115467 husband andВҰ115460 he agrees to live with her, she shouldn'tВҰ115476 divorce him.
\v 14 You see, the unbelieving husband is \add exposed to faith\add* through his wife, and the unbelieving wife is \add exposed to faith\add* through the believing husband, otherwiseВҰ115500 yourВҰ115504 childrenВҰ115503 would be вҖҳdefiledвҖҷ, butВҰ115490 now they are declared innocent.
\v 15 But if the unbelieverВҰ115514 departs, let \add that person\add* go. In such cases, the believing spouse is not tied down \add to serving their departed spouse\add*, butВҰ115528 \add rather\add* \nd GodВҰ115534\nd* has calledВҰ115530 us to peaceВҰ115529.
\v 16 You see, how do you know, woman, whether you will \add cause\add* your husband to be saved? Or how do you know, man, whether you will \add cause\add* your wife to be saved?
\s1 Sticking to your social position
\rem /s1 The Life That the Lord Has Assigned; Live As God Called You
\p
\v 17 Nevertheless, each person shouldВҰ115570 live according to how the \nd masterВҰ115561\nd* has assigned them andВҰ115571 how \nd GodВҰ115567\nd* has calledВҰ115565 them. That's what I teach in all the assembliesВҰ115576.
\v 18 Anyone who was called and who was \add previously\add* circumcised, shouldn't become вҖҳuncircumcisedвҖҷ. Anyone who was called who was uncircumcised, shouldn't get circumcised.
\v 19 Circumcision is nothing andВҰ115596 uncircumcisionВҰ115598 is nothing, butВҰ115601 obeying God's commandsВҰ115603 \add is what counts\add*.
\v 20 Each person shouldВҰ115615 maintain the position they were in when they were calledВҰ115611:
\v 21 Were you a slave when you were calledВҰ115617? Don't be concerned about that (but indeed, if you'reВҰ115624 able to becomeВҰ115626 free, then take the opportunity)
\v 22 becauseВҰ115630 anyone who was a slave when they were called by \nd Yahweh\nd* is free in \nd Yahweh's\nd* \add sight\add*. Conversely, anyone who was free when they were called is the \nd messiah'sВҰ115645\nd* slave.
\v 23 You all were boughtВҰ115648 \add by God\add* for a priceВҰ115647, \add so\add* don'tВҰ115649 becomeВҰ115650 slavesВҰ115652 of peopleВҰ115653.
\v 24 \add Again\add*\x + \xo 7:24 \xt 7:20\x* brothersВҰ115658 andВҰ115658 sistersВҰ115658, each person shouldВҰ115661 remainВҰ115661 in the position they were in when they were calledВҰ115657, \add but now serving\add* \nd GodВҰ115664\nd*.
\s1 Suggestions about the unmarried and about widows
\rem /s1 Questions about the Unmarried and the Widows
\rem /s1 The Unmarried and the Widows
\p
\v 25 Now concerningВҰ115665 unmarried women, I don'tВҰ115671 have instructions from \nd Yahweh\nd* butВҰ115674 I'll give my opinionsВҰ115673 as someone who's trustworthyВҰ115680 thanks to \nd Yahweh's\nd* mercyВҰ115677.
\p
\v 26 ThereforeВҰ115683, I thinkВҰ115682 it's good becauseВҰ115687 of the distress that's about to come, that people should stay as they are \add currently\add*.
\v 27 If you're married, then don't try to get out of it. If you're not committed, don't look for a spouse.
\v 28 ButВҰ115715 if a single guy or single girl get married, that's not a sin, butВҰ115709 they'll \add likely\add* face difficult circumstances andВҰ115715 I'm trying to spare you from that.
\p
\v 29 But brothersВҰ115736 andВҰ115736 sistersВҰ115736, I will say this: the time is shortВҰ115739, so from now on, even those who are married should live as if they're not.
\v 30 Those who are mourning should \add act\add* as if they're not, those who are celebrating should \add act\add* as if they're not, and those who are buyingВҰ115767 \add act\add* as if they don'tВҰ115757 own \add anything\add*,
\v 31 andВҰ115771 those who are using this world, as if they're not using itВҰ115781, becauseВҰ115783 the present form of this world will soon pass away.
\p
\v 32 But I'd like you to be free from concern. Single men are concerned about things of the \nd master\nd*вҖ”pleasingВҰ115801 the \nd master\nd*вҖ”
\v 33 butВҰ115806 marriedВҰ115807 men are concerned about worldlyВҰ115811 affairsвҖ”wanting to pleaseВҰ115813 their wivesвҖ”so they're dividedВҰ115818. And unmarriedВҰ115823 or single women
\v 34 are concerning about things of the \nd masterВҰ115832\nd*вҖ”so that both their bodies and their spiritsВҰ115841 can be separate \add from the world\add*вҖ”butВҰ115839 marriedВҰ115844 women are concerned about worldly affairsвҖ”wanting to pleaseВҰ115850 their husbandsВҰ115853.
\p
\v 35 Now I said \add all\add* that for yourВҰ115858 benefitВҰ115860вҖ”not to load you all with rules, butВҰ115855 to \add act\add* in ways that are appropriate andВҰ115855 devotedВҰ115873 to the \nd masterВҰ115876\nd* without any distractions.
\p
\v 36 However, if a man thinksВҰ115888 he's made the wrong decisions about his unmarried woman,\f + \fr 7:36-38 \ft Yes, вҖҳhis unmarried womanвҖҷ sounds strange, but it's not certain here (and in the next two verses) if Paul is writing about a father and \em his unmarried daughter who's engaged\em*, or about an engaged man deciding about \em his fiancГ©e\em*.\f* if she's reached the age of marriage and it should proceed, then he should do what he plannedвҖ”he's not sinningВҰ115902вҖ”they should get married.
\v 37 ButВҰ115917 if the man has made up his mindВҰ115910 and isn'tВҰ115913 forced, butВҰ115905 makes his own decision, and he's firmly decided to keep his own woman unmarried, then that would also be a good decision.
\v 38 That way, anyone allowing his unmarried woman to marry does well, butВҰ115952 anyone who doesn't, makes a betterВҰ115958 decision.
\p
\v 39 A wife is committed to herВҰ115970 husband as long as he lives, but if he passes away, she's free to marry whoever she wants to, as long as he's a believer.
\v 40 However, in my opinionВҰ115997, she'd be happier if she didn't marry again, and I think it's God's \nd spiritВҰ116002\nd* \add that wants me to say that\add*.
\c 8
\s1 Behaviour about food offered to idols
\rem /s1 Food Sacrificed to Idols; The Question about Food Offered to Idols
\p
\v 1 Now, concerning \add food\add* that's been sacrificedВҰ116009 to idols: We knowВҰ116013 that we all have вҖҳknowledgeвҖҷвҖ”knowledge breeds conceit butВҰ116007 loveВҰ116021 gives inner strength.
\v 2 Anyone who thinks they know something \add usually\add* doesn't know \add what they don'tВҰ116030\add* know,
\v 3 butВҰ116039 anyoneВҰ116040 who loves God is knownВҰ116045 by God.
\p
\v 4 Now \add back to\add* eating \add food\add* that's been offered to idols, weВҰ116054 know that there'sВҰ116051 only one \nd GodВҰ116063\nd* andВҰ116060 so worldlyВҰ116059 idols are \add really\add* nothingВҰ116056 \add at all\add*.
\v 5 Even though there are many so-called вҖҳgodsвҖҷ and вҖҳmastersВҰ116087вҖҷ \add said to\add* live in the heavensВҰ116076 or earthВҰ116080,
\v 6 we know there's \add only\add* one \nd GodВҰ116092\nd*, who is the Father who created everything and we exist \add to honour him\add*. And we only have one \nd masterВҰ116106\nd*, \nd Yeshua MessiahВҰ116108\nd* who created everything and \add is also the source of our existence\add*.
\p
\v 7 ButВҰ116139 not everyone knows this. Some people have been so used to \add trusting\add* idols that \add even now as believers\add* when they eat food that's been sacrificedВҰ116136 to idols, \add they still think it's wrong\add* andВҰ116139 so theirВҰ116142 weak consciencesВҰ116141 become defiledВҰ116146.
\v 8 But food doesn't bring us closer to \nd GodВҰ116155\nd*вҖ”what we eat makes us no better or worse off \add spiritually\add*.
\p
\v 9 However, be careful in case yourВҰ116176 freedom becomesВҰ116179 a reason that weaker \add believers might get confused\add* and stumbleВҰ116178 in their \add spiritual walk\add*.
\v 10 \add Yes,\add* if someone with a weaker conscience sees you eatingВҰ116207 at a place with an idol, they might be encouraged to eat food that's offered to idols \add against their conscience\add*,
\v 11 thus this weaker believer who the \nd messiahВҰ116225\nd* also diedВҰ116226 for, \add might end up\add* beingВҰ116209 destroyedВҰ116209.
\v 12 If you end up sinning against other believersВҰ116232 andВҰ116228 woundingВҰ116234 theirВҰ116235 weak consciencesВҰ116237, you sin against \nd MessiahВҰ116240\nd*.
\v 13 ThereforeВҰ116242, if food might cause a fellow believer to stumble, I'll certainly never eatВҰ116251 meat, so that I won'tВҰ116250 cause them to stumble.
\c 9
\s1 The missionary's responsibilities
\rem /s1 Paul Gives Up His Rights; Rights and Duties of an Apostle; The Rights of an Apostle
\p
\v 1 Aren't I free? Aren't I a missionary? Haven't I seen \nd Yeshua\nd* ourВҰ116276 master? Aren't you all \add the result of\add* myВҰ116281 work for \nd YahwehВҰ116275\nd*?
\v 2 If I'm not a missionary to othersВҰ116287, at least I am to all of you, becauseВҰ116296 you're the proof that I'm a missionary for \nd YahwehВҰ116305\nd*.
\v 3 That's my defenceВҰ116308 to those who are questioning my role.
\p
\v 4 Don't weВҰ116317 have a rightВҰ116318 to eatВҰ116319 andВҰ116320 drinkВҰ116321?
\v 5 Don't weВҰ116324 have a rightВҰ116325 to take alongВҰ116328 a believing wifeВҰ116327 like the rest of the missionaries and the \nd master'sВҰ116338\nd* brothersВҰ116336 and Peter?
\v 6 Or it is only BarnabasВҰ116345 andВҰ116344 I who have to work \add to support ourselves\add*?
\v 7 What soldierВҰ116353 has to pay his own expenses? Who plantsВҰ116358 a vineyardВҰ116359 and isn't \add allowed\add* to eat itsВҰ116366 fruitВҰ116365? Or who shepherdsВҰ116371 a flock and isn't \add allowed\add* to drink the milk \add they produceВҰ116365\add*?
\p
\v 8 Am I \add just\add* sayingВҰ116394 this from a humanВҰ116383 perspective? Doesn't \add Mosheh's\add* law also teach that?
\v 9 He wroteВҰ116400 in those laws: вҖҳDon't prevent the ox from eating when it's \add working to\add* threshВҰ116405 the grain.вҖҷ\x + \xo 9:9: \xt Deu 25:4; 1Tim 5:18.\x*
\v 10 Isn't he saying that on \em our\em* behalf? \add Yes,\add* it was writtenВҰ116420 for our sake \add saying\add* that anyone who's ploughing \add a field \add* should expect \add to be paid\add*, and anyone who threshesВҰ116432 \add the grain\add* should expect a share of the harvest.
\v 11 If we sowedВҰ116448 spiritualВҰ116447 things among you, is it too much to expect a materialВҰ116454 вҖҳharvestвҖҷ from you?\x + \xo 9:11: \xt Rom 15:27.\x*
\v 12 If otherВҰ116458 people have the right to this \add kind of\add* support, don'tВҰ116464 we have a greater right?
\p But we never took advantage of that rightвҖ”instead we enduredВҰ116475 everything so that we wouldn't do anything to hinder the \nd messiah'sВҰ116487\nd* goodВҰ116484 messageВҰ116484 \add from spreading\add*.
\v 13 Don't you know that the temple workers eat from the temple \add budget\add*, and those who work at the altar receive a portion of what's offered?\x + \xo 9:13: \xt Deu 18:1.\x*
\v 14 Similarly, the \nd masterВҰ116511\nd* even instructed that anyone who preaches the good message should be able to make their livingВҰ116520 off it.\x + \xo 9:14: \xt Mat 10:10; Luk 10:7.\x*
\p
\v 15 ButВҰ116530 I haven't taken advantage of \add any\add* of those rights, andВҰ116530 even now, I'm not writing this to ask for material support for myselfвҖ”I'd ratherВҰ116540 dieВҰ116541 than have someone deprive me of this reason for boastingВҰ116546.
\v 16 And yet, when I preach the good message, it doesn't give me any \add good\add* reason to boastВҰ116561 becauseВҰ116563 I'm \add actually\add* \em obligated\em* to do itвҖ”I wouldn't end well if I didn'tВҰ116557 preach the good message
\v 17 becauseВҰ116576 if I do it willinglyВҰ116577, I'll have a rewardВҰ116580, butВҰ116583 if it's done unwillinglyВҰ116584, I'd be \add shirking\add* the responsibility entrustedВҰ116586 to me.
\v 18 SoВҰ116588, what's myВҰ116590 rewardВҰ116593? It's preachingВҰ116595 the good message and \add the privilege of\add* doing it free of chargeВҰ116596, so as not to take advantage of the right that the good message \add gives me\add*.
\p
\v 19 Although I have no obligation to any person, I made myselfВҰ116620 a slave of everyone in orderВҰ116622 to win over as many as possible.
\v 20 To the Jews, I behave like the Jew \add that I am\add* in order to win them. To those under the \add traditional\add* rules, I behave like one of them (although I myselfВҰ116644 am not under those rules) in order to win them over.
\v 21 To those outside \add our religious\add* rules, I behave like them (although not so far as to disobey God's law, because I'm under Messiah's law) in orderВҰ116665 to win them over.
\v 22 To the weak, I become weak to win them over. \add Yes,\add* I'veВҰ116680 become all things to all people so\f + \fr 9:27 \ft TODO: Investigate why so many other translations translate ПҖО¬ОҪП„ПүПӮ something like вҖҳby all meansвҖҷ here (whereas our OET-LV gloss is вҖҳcertainlyвҖҷ).\f* that I might be certainВҰ116685 of saving some.
\p
\v 23 I do all that for the sake of the goodВҰ116694 messageВҰ116694, so that I'll share in its blessings.
\v 24 Surely you all know that all the participants in a race run, but only one \add of them\add* gets the prize? Run in such a way that you get \add the prize\add*.
\v 25 But everyoneВҰ116718 who competes has to exercise self-control in every aspect. They do it in orderВҰ116728 to win a wreath that'll \add quickly\add* wilt, butВҰ116719 weВҰ116732 work towards one that never deteriorates.
\v 26 That's why I don't run aimlessly and don't box like someone punching the air,
\v 27 butВҰ116749 I discipline myВҰ116751 bodyВҰ116753 andВҰ116754 make itВҰ116755 serve me, because after preaching to othersВҰ116758, I don'tВҰ116756 want to \add end up\add* disqualified myselfВҰ116760.
\c 10
\s1 Learn from history
