\v 3 They all ateВҰ116810 the sameВҰ116806 supernatural food\x + \xo 10:3: \xt Exo 16:35.\x*
\v 4 and they all drank the same supernatural drinkВҰ116819, becauseВҰ116822 they drank from a supernatural rock that followedВҰ116825 them, and that rock was the \nd messiahВҰ116833\nd*.\x + \xo 10:4: \xt Exo 17:6; Num 20:11.\x*
\v 5 Despite that, \nd GodВҰ116842\nd* wasn't very happy with most of them, and theyВҰ116843 \add ended up\add* dying in the wildernessВҰ116847.\x + \xo 10:5: \xt Num 14:29-30.\x*
\p
\v 6 Those things \add back thenВҰ116849\add* became examplesВҰ116850 for us, so that we wouldn't be desiringВҰ116864 evil things like they did.\x + \xo 10:6: \xt Num 11:4.\x*
\v 7 Don't worship idols like some of them did, as it's writtenВҰ116874:\x + \xo 10:7: \xt Exo 32:6.\x* вҖҳThe peopleВҰ116877 sat down to eatВҰ116878 and drinkВҰ116880 and \add then\add* stoodВҰ116882 up to \add dance to the golden calf\add*.вҖҷ
\v 8 Nor should weВҰ116885 commitВҰ116885 sexual immorality like many of them did, andВҰ116890 23,000 people died in one dayВҰ116894.\x + \xo 10:8: \xt Num 25:1-18.\x*
\v 9 And nor should weВҰ116899 challenge the \nd masterВҰ116902\nd* like some of \add our Jewish ancestors\add* did, andВҰ116911 then they were killed by the snakes.\x + \xo 10:9: \xt Num 21:5-6.\x*
\v 10 Don't grumbleВҰ116918 like many of them did, andВҰ116926 then they were killed by the \add death angel\add*.\x + \xo 10:10: \xt Num 16:41-49.\x*
\p
\v 11 All of thoseВҰ116941 things happenedВҰ116939 to them as examples andВҰ116943 were writtenВҰ116942 down as warnings for us who are \add living\add* at the endsВҰ116951 of the ages.
\p
\v 12 So if you think your \add faith is solid\add*, be careful that you don't fall.
\v 13 You all haven't been tempted by anything exceptВҰ116968 what is common to humanityВҰ116970, but God is faithfulВҰ116971 and won'tВҰ116965 allowВҰ116977 you to be tempted beyondВҰ116981 what you all can handle. \add In fact,\add* along with the temptations, God will provide the wayВҰ116991 out so thatВҰ116992 you'll be able to endure them.
\rem /s1 Idol Feasts and the Lord's Supper
\p
\v 14 SoВҰ116996 myВҰ116998 dear friends, totally avoid idolatryВҰ117002.
\v 15 I'm speakingВҰ117005 to sensible \add people\add*, \add so\add* judgeВҰ117006 what I'm telling youВҰ117007 for yourselves.
\v 16 When we bless the вҖҳcup of blessingвҖҷ, aren't we sharing the messiah's bloodВҰ117022? When we breakВҰ117029 the breadВҰ117027, aren't we sharing the messiah's bodyВҰ117034?\x + \xo 10:16: \xt Mat 26:26-28; Mrk 14:22-24; Luk 22:19-20.\x*
\v 17 BecauseВҰ117039 there's \add just\add* one loaf that we all eat pieces of, thus we who are many, are one bodyВҰ117043 \add together\add*.
\p
\v 18 Consider \add the people of\add* Yisrael \add (IsraelВҰ117057)\add* from a physical perspective: Aren't those who eat \add portions\add* of the sacrificesВҰ117065, joining to the altarВҰ117068? RECHECK \x + \xo 10:18: \xt Lev 7:6.\x*
\v 19 SoВҰ117071 what am I sayingВҰ117072? That whether or not food is sacrificedВҰ117074 to idols means anything? Or that an idolВҰ117074 is anything?
\v 20 \add No,\add* butВҰ117084 the sacrifices of the pagansВҰ117090 are offered to demons, not to \nd GodВҰ117096\nd*, and I don'tВҰ117095 want youВҰ117101 all to be partnersВҰ117102 with demons.\x + \xo 10:20: \xt Deu 32:17 (LXX).\x*
\v 21 You can't drinkВҰ117112 \nd Yahweh's\nd* cup as well as the cup of demons, nor can you partakeВҰ117122 at \nd Yahweh's\nd* table as well as the table of demons.
\v 22 Or are we \add trying\add* to make \nd YahwehВҰ117129\nd* envious? \add No,\add* he's more powerful than us.\x + \xo 10:22: \xt Deu 32:21.\x*
\rem /s1 The Believer's Freedom; Do All to the Glory of God
\p
\v 23 Everything might \add seem\add* to be allowable, but not everything is beneficialВҰ117140. Everything might \add seem\add* to be allowable, but not everything buildsВҰ117147 up \add character\add*.\x + \xo 10:23: \xt 1Cor 6:12.\x*
\v 24 No one shouldВҰ117152 aim to satisfy themselves, butВҰ117153 \add work for\add* the good of othersВҰ117157.
\p
\v 25 You can eat anything that's sold at the \add meat\add* marketВҰ117162 without even raising questions of conscienceВҰ117169,
\v 26 becauseВҰ117172:\x + \xo 10:26: \xt Psa 24:1.\x* вҖҳthe earthВҰ117175 andВҰ117176 everything in itВҰ117179 belongs to \nd YahwehВҰ117171\nd*.вҖҷ
\p
\v 27 If an unbelieverВҰ117186 invitesВҰ117183 you \add to a meal\add* and you plan to go, eat anything that's set before you without raising questions of conscienceВҰ117203,
\v 28 butВҰ117205 if someone tells you, вҖңThat has been offered as a sacrifice,вҖқ for the sake of the person who told you and for the sake of conscienceВҰ117221, don'tВҰ117213 eat itВҰ117218.
\v 29 Now when I said вҖҳfor the sake of conscienceвҖҷ, I didn'tВҰ117234 mean \em your\em* conscience, butВҰ117237 thatВҰ117235 of the otherВҰ117240 person, because why does \em myВҰ117246\em* freedomВҰ117245 need to be judgedВҰ117247 by someone else's conscience?
\v 30 As long as I've thankedВҰ117254 God for what I eat, why should I then criticise it?
\p
\v 31 SoВҰ117263 whetherВҰ117262 you're eatingВҰ117264 or drinkingВҰ117266 or doing whatever, always ensure that \nd GodВҰ117273\nd* gets honoured.
\v 32 Try not to offend the Jews or the GreeksВҰ117281 or the people in God's assemblyВҰ117284,
\v 33 just like I \add work to\add* pleaseВҰ117291 everyoneвҖ”not for my own benefit butВҰ117298 rather, trying to benefit everyone else so that theyВҰ117303 might get savedВҰ117303.
\c 11
\nb
\v 1 ImitateВҰ117304 me, just like I also imitate \nd MessiahВҰ117309\nd*.\x + \xo 11:1: \xt 1Cor 4:16; Php 3:17.\x*
\s1 Men's and women's head coverings
\rem /s1 Covering the Head in Worship; Public worship; Propriety in Worship; Head Coverings; Instructions for Public Worship
\p
\v 2 Now I commend you all because you always think of what I teach and do, and because you carefully believe and do what I taught you all,
\v 3 but I want you all to know that the messiah is the head of everyВҰ117332 man, and the man is the head of \add his wife\add*, and \nd GodВҰ117349\nd* is the head of the messiah.\f + \fr 11:3 \ft The translators expect that this talk of вҖҳthe headвҖҷ is referring to authority, but because our modern society has become more sensitive to these issues, we decided to keep it literal here, thus letting our readers decide for themselves what Paul probably meant. (Having done that, our readers can also consider for themselves whether this might have been a cultural necessity in and around Corinth, or whether it has widespread application to all cultures.)\f*
\v 4 Any manВҰ117352 who prays or speaks out a prophecyВҰ117355 with his head covered is dishonouring his head,
\v 5 butВҰ117365 any womanВҰ117366 who prays or prophesiesВҰ117369 with her head \em uncoveredВҰ117370\em* dishonours her head, becauseВҰ117380 it's just as if her head had been shavedВҰ117386.
\v 6 \add In fact\add* if a woman doesn't cover her head, then she should cut her hair off, butВҰ117397 if it is shamefulВҰ117398 for a woman to have her hair cut or shavedВҰ117403 off, then she should cover her head.
\v 7 On one side, a man shouldn'tВҰ117408 coverВҰ117410 his head because men present God's imageВҰ117413 and his honour, butВҰ117414 on the otherВҰ117421 side, women present \add their husbands'\add* honour,\x + \xo 11:7: \xt Gen 1:26-27.\x*
\v 8 becauseВҰ117426 man wasn't made from the woman, but \add the first\add* woman was made out of man.\x + \xo 11:8-9: \xt Gen 2:18-23.\x*
\v 9 \add Indeed,\add* men weren't createdВҰ117438 for women, butВҰ117443 women for men.
\v 10 BecauseВҰ117449 of that, women should have authority on their heads, because of the messengersВҰ117461.\f + \fr 11:10 \ft Again, a rather literal translation because honestly, no one is really certain about what Paul was meaning here. See also https://GitHub.com/openenglishbible/Open-English-Bible/issues/356 and https://UASVBible.org/2024/02/03/unveiling-the-meaning-of-authority-in-1-corinthians-1110-a-textual-and-exegetical-clarification.\f*
\v 11 Nevertheless, in Messiah, women are not independent from men, nor are men independent from women,
\v 12 becauseВҰ117478 just as the \add first\add* woman came out of the man, so too men \add are born\add* from women, butВҰ117492 everything comes from \nd GodВҰ117496\nd*.
\p
\v 13 \add So\add* judgeВҰ117500 for yourselvesВҰ117499: is itВҰ117502 proper for women to pray to \nd GodВҰ117507\nd* \add with their heads\add* uncoveredВҰ117505?
\v 14 Doesn't natureВҰ117513 itselfВҰ117514 teachВҰ117516 youВҰ117517 all that if a manВҰ117519 has longВҰ117523 hair, itВҰ117526 is a disgrace for himВҰ117525,
\v 15 but if a womanВҰ117527 has long hair, it's \add part of\add* her beauty because long hair has been givenВҰ117540 to women as a coveringВҰ117538?
\v 16 However, if anyone'sВҰ117544 inclined to be contentiousВҰ117546 about this, that's not how either weВҰ117548 \add ourselves\add* or God's assembliesВҰ117555 behave.
\s1 Conduct when celebrating the master's dinner
\rem /s1 Abuses at the Lord's Supper; Order at the Lord's Supper
\r (Mat. 26:26-29; Mark 14:22-25; Luke 22:14-20)
\p
\v 17 But I'm not complimenting you all in giving the following instructions, becauseВҰ117565 your gatherings have been doing more harm than good.
\v 18 FirstlyВҰ117575, I hearВҰ117583 that when you gather togetherВҰ117578 in \add the\add* assemblyВҰ117582, there are divisionsВҰ117584 amongВҰ117585 you all, and I partly believeВҰ117591 it
\v 19 becauseВҰ117593 there must be differences among you to show who out of all of you are approvedВҰ117602.
\v 20 SoВҰ117608 then, when youВҰ117609 gather togetherВҰ117607 in one placeВҰ117612, it's not to \add celebrate by\add* eating the master'sВҰ117615 dinner
\v 21 becauseВҰ117620 during the meal, everyoneВҰ117630 \add grabs\add* their own food without considering others. So some people remain hungry while others have too much to drink.
\v 22 For eatingВҰ117643 and drinkingВҰ117645, don'tВҰ117636 you all have your own housesВҰ117638 to do that in? Why are you showing contempt for God's assemblyВҰ117648 and humiliating those \add left with\add* nothing? What should I sayВҰ117659 about that? Should I praiseВҰ117661 you for that? \add No,\add* I can'tВҰ117636!
\rem /s1 The Institution of the Lord's Supper
\p
\v 23 I've \add already\add* passed on to all of you everything that I receivedВҰ117670 from the master: that on the nightВҰ117684 when he was betrayed, he took some breadВҰ117688
\v 24 and after giving thanksВҰ117690, he broke \add off a piece\add* and saidВҰ117693, вҖңThis \add represents\add* myВҰ117697 bodyВҰ117701 whichВҰ117702 \add will be\add* broken for your sakes. Keep doingВҰ117707 this in memory of me.вҖқ
\v 25 SimilarlyВҰ117712, afterВҰ117716 the dinner he took the cup and said, вҖңThis cup \add represents\add* the new agreement \add which will be sealed\add* by my bloodВҰ117730. As oftenВҰ117734 as you all \add celebrate\add*, drinkВҰ117737 it in memory of me.вҖқ\x + \xo 11:25: a \xt Exo 24:8; Jer 31:31-34; \xo b \xt Exo 24:6-8.\x*
\v 26 BecauseВҰ117743 as oftenВҰ117742 as you all \add celebrate by\add* eatingВҰ117746 breadВҰ117748 and drinkingВҰ117755 from the cup, you'll continue to announce the \nd master'sВҰ117759\nd* deathВҰ117757 untilВҰ117761 he returns.
\rem /s1 Partaking of the Supper Unworthily
\p
\v 27 Therefore, anyone who eats that breadВҰ117770 or drinksВҰ117774 from the \nd master's\nd* cup in an unworthyВҰ117779 manner will be guilty of sinning against the bodyВҰ117785 and bloodВҰ117788 of the \nd master\nd*.
\v 28 So everyone must first examine themself as part of eatingВҰ117802 that breadВҰ117801 and drinkingВҰ117807 from that cup,
\v 29 becauseВҰ117809 anyone who eats and drinks without discerning the body,\f + \fr 11:29 \ft Discern/distinguish/recognise their own body? The master's body? The whole group as a body? Unfortunately, we can't ask Paul exactly what he meant here.\f* eats and drinks judgementВҰ117814 onto themself.
\v 30 BecauseВҰ117825 of that, many amongВҰ117827 youВҰ117828 are weak and sickВҰ117832, and many have passed away,
\v 31 butВҰ117837 if we were examining ourselvesВҰ117839, we wouldn't be judgedВҰ117843.
\v 32 However, when we're judgedВҰ117844 by \nd YahwehВҰ117848\nd*, we're being disciplinedВҰ117849 so that we won'tВҰ117851 be condemnedВҰ117855 along with the unbelievers.
\p
\v 33 So brothersВҰ117857 andВҰ117857 sistersВҰ117857, when you come togetherВҰ117859 to celebrate this, wait for each other.
\v 34 If anyone'sВҰ117867 hungry, they shouldВҰ117871 eat at homeВҰ117870 \add beforehand\add*, so that your meetings won'tВҰ117873 lead to judgementВҰ117875. I'llВҰ117884 give instructions about otherВҰ117879 matters when I get there.
\c 12
\s1 The various abilities given by God's spirit
\rem /s1 Spiritual Gifts; Gifts from the Holy Spirit
\p
\v 1 Now brothersВҰ117890 andВҰ117887 sistersВҰ117890, I don'tВҰ117891 want youВҰ117893 all to be ignorant about spiritualВҰ117889 \add mattersВҰ117889\add*.
\v 2 You all know that when you were still pagansВҰ117898, you were enticed and led astray in front of idolsВҰ117902 that can't \add even\add* speak.
\v 3 SoВҰ117909 now I'm informing you all that a person who curses Yeshua, doesn't speak with the power of God's spirit. On the other hand, a person who says that Yeshua is \nd YahwehВҰ117926\nd* must be speaking with \add the power of\add* the holy spirit.
\p
\v 4 Now thereВҰ117938 are varieties of giftsВҰ117937, butВҰ117940 the sameВҰ117941 \nd spiritВҰ117942\nd*,\x + \xo 12:4-11: \xt Rom 12:6-8.\x*
\v 5 andВҰ117943 thereВҰ117946 are varieties of ministries, butВҰ117947 the sameВҰ117949 \nd masterВҰ117950\nd*.
\v 6 There are varieties of activities, butВҰ117955 the sameВҰ117958 \nd GodВҰ117960\nd* works all things in everyone.
\v 7 Now the display of the \nd spirit'sВҰ117974\nd* \add power\add* is givenВҰ117970 to each \add person\add* in order to benefitВҰ117977 \add everyone\add*.
\v 8 One \add person\add* might be given a wise message throughВҰ117982 the spirit, and someone else given \add certain\add* knowledgeВҰ117991 by the same spirit.
\v 9 Another \add person\add* might be given faithВҰ117998 by the same spirit, and someone else given giftsВҰ118005 of healingsВҰ118006 from that one spirit.
\v 10 Another might be given the ability to do miraclesВҰ118015, and someone else given prophecyВҰ118019. Another might be given ability to distinguishВҰ118022 spiritsВҰ118024, and someone else given the ability to speak other languages, and to yet another the ability to translateВҰ118033 languages.
\v 11 However it's the one and the same spirit behind all those thingsвҖ”distributing them individually to each personВҰ118046 as the spirit decides.
\s1 One body with many parts
\rem /s1 One Body with Many Members; One Body with Many Parts
\p
\v 12 Just like a \add human\add* body is a unit butВҰ118056 has many parts which are all components, no matter how many, making up that one body, so too is the \nd messiahВҰ118079\nd*.\x + \xo 12:12: \xt Rom 12:4-5.\x*
\v 13 \add Yes,\add* in one spirit we were all immersedВҰ118090 into one bodyВҰ118089, whether \add we were\add* Jews or GreeksВҰ118094, whether slavesВҰ118096 or free, and we all were given one spirit to drinkВҰ118105. MEANING?
\p
\v 14 \add Yes,\add* indeed the bodyВҰ118110 is not one part, butВҰ118115 many.
\v 15 If \add your\add* foot said, вҖңSince I'm not a hand, I'm not part of the body,вҖқ that wouldn't make it any less a part of the body,
\v 16 andВҰ118139 if \add your\add* ear said, вҖңSince I'm not an eye, I'm not part of the body,вҖқ that wouldn't make it any less a part of the body.
\v 17 If \add your\add* whole body was an eye, how could \add you\add* hearВҰ118171? \add But then,\add* if \add your\add* whole body was an ear, how could \add you\add* smellВҰ118177 \add anything\add*?
\v 18 Actually, \nd GodВҰ118183\nd* has placed every part in our bodies \add exactly\add* where he wantedВҰ118194 to put them.
\v 19 If it was all just one part, how could it be a bodyВҰ118204?
\v 20 \add Yes,\add* there's many parts, butВҰ118206 \add only\add* one bodyВҰ118212.
\p
\v 21 \add YourВҰ118223\add* eyeВҰ118217 can't tell \add your\add* handВҰ118221, вҖңI don't need you,вҖқ and \add your\add* head can't tell \add your\add* feetВҰ118231, вҖңI don't need you.вҖқ
\v 22 On the contrary, the bodyВҰ118243 partsВҰ118241 that seem to be weakerВҰ118244 are \add very\add* vital,
\v 23 and those body parts thatВҰ118249 seem less honourable, we give them greater honour and hence ourВҰ118262 unpresentable body parts are \add treated with\add* more modesty.
\v 24 OurВҰ118269 presentable parts don't have any need for that, butВҰ118273 rather \nd GodВҰ118276\nd* has put the bodyВҰ118279 togetherВҰ118277 and he gaveВҰ118286 greater honourВҰ118287 to the lesser parts
\v 25 so that thereВҰ118290 won'tВҰ118289 be any divisionВҰ118292 in the bodyВҰ118295, butВҰ118296 its membersВҰ118303 should care equally for each other.
\v 26 SoВҰ118304 if one body part is hurting, all the parts hurt as well. If one body part is honoured, thenВҰ118304 all the parts are happy together.
\p
\v 27 Now you all are the bodyВҰ118328 of Christ, andВҰ118326 each of you is a part of it.
\v 28 And indeedВҰ118336, \nd GodВҰ118339\nd* has appointedВҰ118337: 1/ missionaries, 2/ prophetsВҰ118346, 3/ teachersВҰ118348, thenВҰ118334 \add doing\add* miraclesВҰ118350, healingВҰ118354 \add others\add*, helping \add others\add*, guiding \add others\add*, \add andВҰ118334 speaking\add* various languagesВҰ118358\x + \xo 12:28: \xt Eph 4:11.\x*
\v 29 Are everyone missionaries, or everyone prophetsВҰ118364 or teachersВҰ118367, or doing miraclesВҰ118370?
\v 30 Does everyone have the giftsВҰ118373 of healingВҰ118375, or speakingВҰ118379 in other languagesВҰ118378, or translating?
\p
\v 31 ButВҰ118390 strive for the better giftsВҰ118386.
\rem /s1 Love Is the Greatest
\p And now I'll demonstrate a better wayВҰ118396 to youВҰ118397 all:
\c 13
\s1 Love expounded
\rem /s1 The Gift of Love
\p
\v 1 Even if I could speakВҰ118404 in humanВҰ118403 languages as well as the languages of \add God's\add* messengersВҰ118407, butВҰ118409 didn'tВҰ118410 loveВҰ118408 \add others\add*, then I'd \add just\add* be like a noisy gong or a clanging cymbalВҰ118416.
\v 2 And if have \add the ability of being able\add* to prophesyВҰ118423 and could understand all mysteriesВҰ118427 and all knowledgeВҰ118433, and if I had totalВҰ118429 faithВҰ118440 so I could tell mountainsВҰ118442 to move, butВҰ118419 I didn'tВҰ118446 loveВҰ118444 \add others\add*, thenВҰ118419 I'm \add of no use to anyone\add*.\x + \xo 13:2: \xt Mat 17:20; 21:21; Mrk 11:23.\x*
\v 3 Even if I gave everything I have \add to the poor\add*, andВҰ118460 even sacrifice myВҰ118458 bodyВҰ118465 so that I could boastВҰ118468, butВҰ118472 didn'tВҰ118473 loveВҰ118471 \add others\add*, it wouldn't be any use to me.
\p
\v 4 Love is patientВҰ118479 and kind. It doesn't envy \add others\add*, it doesn't boast, and it isn'tВҰ118483 arrogantВҰ118492.
\v 5 It isn'tВҰ118493 crude, it doesn't just care about itselfВҰ118501, it doesn't get angry quickly, and it doesn't keep records about who wrongs \add us\add*.
\v 6 Love isn'tВҰ118508 happy with disobeying \add God\add*, butВҰ118514 is happy about the truthВҰ118516.
\v 7 It tolerates everything, believesВҰ118522 everything, is always hopeful about everything, and always perseveres.
\p
\v 8 Love neverВҰ118529 fails, unlike propheciesВҰ118534 that will come to nothing, languagesВҰ118539 that will die out, and knowledgeВҰ118542 that \add also\add* will come to nothing,
\v 9 because we only have partial knowledge and partial \add understanding\add* of prophecyВҰ118553.
\v 10 So when perfectionВҰ118558 comes, partial things will disappear.
\p
\v 11 When I was a child, I spoke like a child, thought like a child, and reasoned like a child, \add but\add* then when I became an adult, I set childish things aside.
\v 12 \add In this present age\add*, we see like fuzzy reflections in a mirrorВҰ118591, but \add in the future\add*, we'll see \add God\add* face to face. In this age, I have partial knowledge, but then it'll be complete, just like \em we'll be knownВҰ118609\em* completely.
\p
\v 13 ButВҰ118623 for now, these threeВҰ118617 continue: faithВҰ118613, hope, and love, butВҰ118611 love is the greatestВҰ118622 one of those.
\c 14
\s1 Comparing prophesying with speaking in other languages
\rem /s1 The Gifts of Tongues and Prophecy; Gifts of Prophecy and Tongues; More about Gifts from the Spirit
\p
\v 1 Aim to \add show\add* loveВҰ118629, andВҰ118631 eagerly strive for spiritualВҰ118633 \add things\add*вҖ”especially the ability to prophesyВҰ118637,
\v 2 because anyoneВҰ118649 speaking another language isn'tВҰ118643 speaking to \add the\add* peopleВҰ118644, but to \nd GodВҰ118648\nd*, because no one understands \add it\add*, but they're speaking \add about\add* spiritualВҰ118652 mysteriesВҰ118655.
\v 3 However, anyone who's prophesyingВҰ118658, speaksВҰ118660 to \add the\add* peopleВҰ118659 for their instruction and encouragement and comfort.
\v 4 Anyone who's speakingВҰ118667 in another language instructs themself, butВҰ118672 when \add people\add* prophesyВҰ118673, they're instructing the \add whole\add* assemblyВҰ118674.
\p
\v 5 Now I'd like it if you all spoke in other languages, butВҰ118677 I'd like it better if you could all be prophesying. The person prophesying is more helpful than someone speaking in other languages, unless they translate so that the assemblyВҰ118705 can be instructed.
\v 6 But now brothersВҰ118711 andВҰ118711 sistersВҰ118711, if I comeВҰ118713 to you speakingВҰ118717 in other languagesВҰ118716, how can I be of benefitВҰ118720 to you all? Only if I share a revelationВҰ118727 with you all, or some knowledgeВҰ118730, or a prophecyВҰ118733 or teachingВҰ118736.
\p
\v 7 Even the tune coming from non-living things like musical instruments can'tВҰ118751 be recognised unless the distinct notes can be distinguished,
\v 8 becauseВҰ118762 if the trumpetВҰ118766 produces an unclear soundВҰ118767, how will \add the soldiers\add* know to prepareВҰ118770 for battleВҰ118773.
\v 9 Similarly with all of youвҖ”unless your words are intelligible, how will anyone know what you're saying? You'll just be talkingВҰ118794 to the wind.
\v 10 There's certainly many different languagesВҰ118799 in the worldВҰ118803, butВҰ118804 none of them are without meaning,
\v 11 so if I don'tВҰ118810 know the meaning of someone's language, I'm a foreigner to that person, andВҰ118821 that person \add will be\add* a foreigner to me
\v 12 and it's the same with all of you. Because you all want spiritualВҰ118833 \add things\add* in order to help grow the assemblyВҰ118838, then strive to have many \add of them\add*.
\p
\v 13 SoВҰ118843 then, let anyone who's speakingВҰ118846 in another language, pray that they will be able to translate \add it\add*.
\v 14 When I pray in another language, my spiritВҰ118856 prays butВҰ118860 my mind is unproductive,
\v 15 so what should I do? \add Well,\add* I'll pray with my spirit, but I'll also pray with my mind. I'll sing with my spirit, but I'll also sing with my mind.
\v 16 OtherwiseВҰ118886, if you \add speak out\add*a blessingВҰ118889 in the spiritВҰ118892, how can the ordinary \add listeners\add* say вҖҳMayВҰ118902 itВҰ118902 beВҰ118902 soВҰ118902вҖҷ after you give thanksВҰ118906, sinceВҰ118908 they wouldn't know what you've been saying.
\v 17 \add Yes,\add* you'd certainly give thanksВҰ118917 well, butВҰ118918 the otherВҰ118920 \add people\add* wouldn't be encouraged.
\p
\v 18 I thankВҰ118923 \nd GodВҰ118925\nd* that I speakВҰ118933 in other language more than all of youВҰ118929,
\v 19 but with the assemblyВҰ118938, I'd prefer to speakВҰ118949 five words with myВҰ118948 mind so that I can instructВҰ118953 othersВҰ118952, rather than thousandsВҰ118955 of words in another language.
\p
\v 20 BrothersВҰ118959 andВҰ118959 sistersВҰ118959, don'tВҰ118960 be childishВҰ118961 in your thinking. You all can be like infants with respect to \em evil\em*, butВҰ118970 \add in everything else\add*, be matureВҰ118972 in your thinking.
\v 21 \add The prophet Yeshayah\add* wroteВҰ118978:\x + \xo 14:21: \xt Isa 28:11-12.\x*
\q1 вҖҳI'llВҰ118988 speakВҰ118988 to this nation
\q2 through foreignВҰ118982 languagesВҰ118982 and strangers' lipsВҰ118985,
\q1 butВҰ118983 even then theyВҰ118996 won'tВҰ118993 listenВҰ118996 to me,вҖҷ
\m says \nd YahwehВҰ118999\nd*.
\v 22 So then, \add speaking\add* in other languagesВҰ119002 is a signВҰ119004, not for believers, but for unbelievers. However \add in contrast,\add* prophecyВҰ119014 is not for unbelievers, but for believers.
\p
\v 23 SoВҰ119022 if the wholeВҰ119027 assemblyВҰ119026 gathered togetherВҰ119024 at the sameВҰ119030 placeВҰ119030 and they all spoke in other languagesВҰ119035, and then some inquirersВҰ119040 or unbelieversВҰ119042 came in, wouldn't they say that you're all crazy?
\v 24 ButВҰ119053 if they were all prophesyingВҰ119050 \add instead\add* and some inquirersВҰ119057 or unbelieversВҰ119055 came in, they'd be convicted \add of their sinfulness\add* and called to account by them all.
\v 25 \add The prophecies\add* would expose the secretsВҰ119067 of their heartsВҰ119070, so then they'd bow down and worship God, and exclaim, вҖңGod is really \add here\add* amongВҰ119089 youВҰ119090 all!вҖқ
\s1 The correct means of worshipping
\rem /s1 Orderly Worship; Order in the Church; A Call to Orderly Worship
\p
\v 26 SoВҰ119095 brothersВҰ119097 andВҰ119097 sistersВҰ119097, what shouldВҰ119117 we say then? When you all gather togetherВҰ119099, each one of you brings a song or a teachingВҰ119104, or \add explains\add* a revelationВҰ119108, or \add has a message\add* in another language or has \add the\add* translationВҰ119112. Let everything you do \add be aimed at growing the faith of the hearers\add*.
\v 27 If there's any speakingВҰ119122 in other languages, \add itВҰ119131 should be\add* twoВҰ119124 or threeВҰ119128 \add people\add* at most, taking turns and someone should translate.
\v 28 ButВҰ119146 if there's no translator, they shouldВҰ119142 be silentВҰ119142 in the assemblyВҰ119144, and \add save it\add* for between themselves and \nd GodВҰ119150\nd*.
\v 29 ButВҰ119152 let twoВҰ119153 or threeВҰ119155 \add people\add* prophesy, and then the othersВҰ119159 shouldВҰ119156 evaluate what was said.
\v 30 However if somethingВҰ119164 is revealedВҰ119164 to someone still seated, then the firstВҰ119168 person shouldВҰ119169 \add stop speaking\add*,
\v 31 becauseВҰ119171 youВҰ119170 can all prophesyВҰ119175 in turn so that everyoneВҰ119172 can be instructed andВҰ119179 encouraged.
\v 32 The prophet's spiritsВҰ119183 are under the control of the prophets,
\v 33 becauseВҰ119188 \nd GodВҰ119194\nd* isn'tВҰ119187 \add a god\add* of disorder, butВҰ119195 of peaceВҰ119196.
\p As in all the assembliesВҰ119201 of believers,
\v 34 the womenВҰ119205 shouldВҰ119210 stay silentВҰ119210 in the assembliesВҰ119209, becauseВҰ119212 they're not permittedВҰ119214 to speakВҰ119216, butВҰ119217 must be in submission as \add Mosheh's\add* law says.
\v 35 ButВҰ119228 if they want to know more about anythingВҰ119229, they shouldВҰ119240 ask theirВҰ119237 own husbandsВҰ119239 at homeВҰ119236, becauseВҰ119242 it's shamefulВҰ119241 for a womanВҰ119245 to speakВҰ119246 in the assemblyВҰ119248.
\p
\v 36 Did God's messageВҰ119255 \em originate\em* from you all, or did itВҰ119263 only \em come\em* to you?
\v 37 If anyoneВҰ119265 thinks they're a prophetВҰ119267 or a spiritualВҰ119270 \add person\add*, then they shouldВҰ119272 \add readily\add* acknowledge that what I'm writingВҰ119274 to youВҰ119275 all is \nd Yahweh's\nd* commandВҰ119284,
\v 38 butВҰ119286 if anyone'sВҰ119287 ignorant, then let them stay ignorant.
\p
\v 39 So brothersВҰ119292 and sistersВҰ119292, strive to \add be able to\add* prophesyВҰ119296, and don'tВҰ119301 forbidВҰ119302 the speakingВҰ119299 of other languagesВҰ119304,
\v 40 butВҰ119306 let everything be done properlyВҰ119307 andВҰ119308 orderlyВҰ119310.
\c 15
