\p
\v 1 Now brothersВҰ119316 and sistersВҰ119316, I want to remind you all about the good message thatВҰ119322 I preachedВҰ119320 to you, which you thenВҰ119314 receivedВҰ119324 and now \add base your faith\add* on.
\v 2 You're all savedВҰ119332 by that good message if you hold firmly to what I preachedВҰ119335 to you, \add assuming\add* that you didn't just \add вҖҳsay thatвҖҷ you\add* believeВҰ119344.
\p
\v 3 \add Yes,\add* firstВҰ119349 of all, I passed onto youВҰ119347 all what I \add myself\add* had receivedВҰ119352: that \nd MessiahВҰ119354\nd* diedВҰ119355 for ourВҰ119359 sinsВҰ119358 as the scripturesВҰ119362 \add had predicted\add*,\x + \xo 15:3: \xt Isa 53:5-12.\x*
\v 4 and that he was buriedВҰ119365 and then brought back to life on the thirdВҰ119373 dayВҰ119371 as per the scripturesВҰ119376 \add again\add*,\x + \xo 15:4: \xt Psa 16:8-10; Mat 12:40; Acts 2:24-32.\x*
\v 5 and that he was seenВҰ119379 by CephasВҰ119380 and then by the twelveВҰ119384.\x + \xo 15:5: a \xt Luk 24:34; \xo b \xt Mat 28:16-17; Mrk 16:14; Luk 24:36; Yhn 20:19.\x*
\v 6 Then he was seenВҰ119386 by more than 500 believersВҰ119389 at onceвҖ”most of whom are still living, although some have already passed away.
\v 7 Then he was seenВҰ119403 by Yacob, and then by all the ambassadorsВҰ119408.
\p
\v 8 Then last of all, as if I'd been born at the wrong time, he appearedВҰ119416 to me also,\x + \xo 15:8: \xt Acts 9:3-6.\x*
\v 9 because I'm the leastВҰ119422 of the ambassadorsВҰ119424вҖ”quite unworthy of that title because I persecutedВҰ119432 God's assemblyВҰ119434.\x + \xo 15:9: \xt Acts 8:3.\x*
\v 10 ButВҰ119443 I am what I am thanks to God's grace, as hisВҰ119446 grace towardsВҰ119448 me hasn't been wasted. Actually, I worked harder than all \add the others\add*, although \add of course\add* it wasn't really me, butВҰ119438 God's grace with me.
\v 11 \add Anyway,\add* whetherВҰ119474 it was me or them, weВҰ119480 \add all\add* preach \add that same good message\add*, andВҰ119481 that's how youВҰ119483 all came to beliefВҰ119483.
\s1 Life after death
\rem /s1 Our Resurrection; The Resurrection of the Dead
\p
\v 12 Now if \add the message\add* declares that \nd MessiahВҰ119486\nd* was killed andВҰ119485 thenВҰ119485 raisedВҰ119492 back to life, how come some of youВҰ119497 are sayingВҰ119494 that no one comes back to life?
\v 13 If no one who's deadВҰ119507 comes back to life, then \nd MessiahВҰ119511\nd* couldn't have come back to life,
\v 14 and if \nd MessiahВҰ119515\nd* hasn't come back to life, then ourВҰ119523 preaching is meaningless and so is yourВҰ119530 faithВҰ119528!
\v 15 Not only that, it would make us into fraudsters lying about God, becauseВҰ119537 we've testifiedВҰ119538 that God brought \nd MessiahВҰ119545\nd* back to life, butВҰ119532 that can't be true if the deadВҰ119552 can't come back to life.
\v 16 BecauseВҰ119556 if the deadВҰ119557 don'tВҰ119558 come back to life, then \nd MessiahВҰ119561\nd* can'tВҰ119558 have come back to life,
\v 17 butВҰ119564 if \nd MessiahВҰ119565\nd* didn'tВҰ119566 come back to life, then yourВҰ119571 faithВҰ119570 is wasted and you're all stillВҰ119574 \add just unforgiven\add* sinners.
\v 18 Again, if that's the case, those believers who've passed away \add simply\add* perishedВҰ119587.
\v 19 If our hope in \nd MessiahВҰ119596\nd* only \add applies\add* to this lifeВҰ119591, then we should be pitied more than \nd anyoneВҰ119596\nd* else.
\p
\v 20 But \nd MessiahВҰ119606\nd* has indeed come back to life from the deadВҰ119609, leading the way for those who have passed away,
\v 21 becauseВҰ119615 sinceВҰ119614 deathВҰ119619 came through a man \add (Adam)\add*, then the resurrectionВҰ119623 of the dead also comes through a man \add (Yeshua)\add*.
\v 22 Just as everyone who's in AdamВҰ119629 will die, so everyone who's in \nd MessiahВҰ119636\nd* will come back to lifeВҰ119638,
\v 23 butВҰ119640 each in hisВҰ119654 own turn: firstВҰ119645 \nd MessiahВҰ119646\nd* will be leading, then when he \add returns\add*, those who belong to him.
\v 24 Then the endВҰ119657 will come when he hands over the kingship to \nd GodВҰ119666\nd* the Father after he's destroyed all rule, and all authorityВҰ119677 and powerВҰ119679,
\v 25 becauseВҰ119681 he must reignВҰ119683 untilВҰ119684 he's defeated all hisВҰ119695 enemiesВҰ119690.\x + \xo 15:25: \xt Psa 110:1.\x*
\v 26 The final enemyВҰ119704 to be abolished will be deathВҰ119707 itself
\v 27 becauseВҰ119709 \add (as David wrote)\add*,\x + \xo 15:27: \xt Psa 8:6.\x* вҖҳGod has made everything subject to him.вҖҷ (Now when it says вҖҳeverythingвҖҷ, \add of course\add* that doesn't include \add God\add* who's the one that made it happen.)
\v 28 And when everything has been put under his control, thenВҰ119733 the son himselfВҰ119740 will submit to the one who subjected everything to him, so that \nd GodВҰ119752\nd* \add will be in totalВҰ119737 control\add*.
\p
\v 29 OtherwiseВҰ119758, what will the people do who are being immersed \add in water\add* for the dead? If the dead don'tВҰ119769 come back to life, why would they get immersed for them? TODO: WHAT'S THIS ABOUT?
\v 30 \add As for us,\add* why do weВҰ119780 \add place ourselves\add* in dangerВҰ119781 all the time?
\v 31 I'm dyingВҰ119786 everyВҰ119784 dayВҰ119785 by yourВҰ119791 boastingВҰ119792 brothersВҰ119793 andВҰ119793 sistersВҰ119793, whichВҰ119794 I have in \nd MessiahВҰ119797 Yeshua\nd* ourВҰ119801 \nd masterВҰ119800\nd*. TODO: WHAT DOES THIS MEAN?
\v 32 If I foughtВҰ119805 with wild animals at EphesusВҰ119807 for humanВҰ119804 \add purposes\add*, what did I gain? If the deadВҰ119813 aren'tВҰ119814 brought back to life, then вҖҳLet's eatВҰ119816 andВҰ119817 drinkВҰ119818, becauseВҰ119820 tomorrowВҰ119819 we'll die \add anyway\add*.вҖҷ\x + \xo 15:32: \xt Isa 22:13.\x*
\p
\v 33 Don't be fooled: вҖҳEvil conversationsВҰ119827 corruptВҰ119824 goodВҰ119826 characterВҰ119825.вҖҷ
\v 34 SoberВҰ119829 up as you should, and stop sinningВҰ119833, becauseВҰ119835 some of you are \add quite\add* ignorantВҰ119834 about \nd GodВҰ119836\nd*. (I say that to your shameВҰ119840.)
\s1 Our new immortal bodies
\rem /s1 The Resurrection Body
\p
\v 35 ButВҰ119852 someoneВҰ119846 will ask, вҖңHow do the deadВҰ119850 come back to life andВҰ119852 what kind of bodyВҰ119853 will theyВҰ119854 \add have thenВҰ119852\add*?вҖқ
\v 36 Silly question! \add Plants\add* don'tВҰ119859 come to lifeВҰ119860 unless the seed dies \add first\add*.
\v 37 And you don'tВҰ119870 sow the plants, butВҰ119867 you sow the bare seedsвҖ”perhaps of wheatВҰ119882 or somethingВҰ119885 elseвҖ”
\v 38 then \nd GodВҰ119890\nd* gives it a body just like he wants, so each seed gets its own \add new\add* body.
\p
\v 39 Not all bodies are the sameВҰ119908: humansВҰ119914 have one kind of bodyВҰ119906, animalsВҰ119918 have different ones, birdsВҰ119922 different again, and fish also different.
\p
\v 40 There are also heavenly bodies and earthly bodies, butВҰ119934 the beauty of heavenly bodies and of earthly \add bodies\add* are \add quite\add* different.
\v 41 The sun, the moonВҰ119953, and the stars all have their own different types of beauty, and even the beauty of stars differs from one to another.
\p
\v 42 So too itВҰ119973 is with the resurrectionВҰ119967 of the deadВҰ119969. The decaying body is вҖҳsownвҖҷ \add into the ground\add*, but the raisedВҰ119973 \add body\add* is immortal.
\v 43 It's вҖҳsownвҖҷ in dishonourВҰ119978 but it's raised in splendour. It's вҖҳsownвҖҷ in weaknessВҰ119984 but it's raised in powerВҰ119987.
\v 44 It's вҖҳsownвҖҷ a natural body but it's raisedВҰ119991 as a spiritual body. (If there's a natural body, there's also a spiritual body.)
\v 45 As it's also writtenВҰ120006:\x + \xo 15:45: \xt Gen 2:7.\x* вҖҳThe firstВҰ120009 Adam became a livingВҰ120014 being.вҖҷ The last вҖҳAdamвҖҷ is a life-giving spiritВҰ120019,
\v 46 butВҰ120026 the spiritual doesn't come firstвҖ”it's first the naturalВҰ120028 and \em then\em* the spiritual.
\v 47 The firstВҰ120033 man was made of dust from the earthВҰ120037вҖ”the secondВҰ120040 man \add came\add* from heavenВҰ120046.
\v 48 Earthly people are like \add that\add* earthly man, andВҰ120055 heavenly people are like \add that\add* heavenly man.
\p
\v 49 And just like we carry the image of \add that\add* earthlyВҰ120071 man, we should also bear the image of \add that\add* heavenlyВҰ120080 man.
\v 50 Now brothersВҰ120084 and sistersВҰ120084, I can tell you all that our \add present physical bodies\add* can'tВҰ120092 inherit God's kingdomВҰ120089, and nor can corruptВҰ120097 \add things\add* inherit immortality.
\p
\v 51 ListenВҰ120102, I'm explaining a mysteryВҰ120103 to youВҰ120104 all. Not all of us will pass away, but we will all be changedВҰ120116\x + \xo 15:51-52: \xt 1Th 4:15-17.\x*
\v 52 in an instantВҰ120118, a \add millisecond\add*, at the last trumpet becauseВҰ120130 the trumpet will sound and the deadВҰ120133 will come back to living as immortals, and we'll be changedВҰ120139.
\v 53 \add Yes,\add* it's essential for this perishableВҰ120143 \add body\add* to become incorruptible andВҰ120147 for this mortalВҰ120149 to become immortalВҰ120152.
\v 54 ButВҰ120160 when this perishableВҰ120156 \add body\add* becomes incorruptible andВҰ120160 this mortalВҰ120162 becomes immortalВҰ120166, then what was writtenВҰ120179 will come true:\x + \xo 15:54: \xt Isa 25:8.\x* вҖҳDeath is replaced by victoryВҰ120184.вҖҷ
\q1
\v 55 \x + \xo 15:55: \xt Hos 13:14 (LXX).\x*вҖҳDeath, where is your victoryВҰ120189?
\q1 \add Yes\add* death, where is your stingВҰ120194?вҖҷ
\m
\v 56 Sin is the stingВҰ120202 of deathВҰ120204, andВҰ120209 sin's powerВҰ120210 is The Law,
\v 57 butВҰ120216 be thankfulВҰ120218 to \nd GodВҰ120217\nd* because it's him who gives us the victoryВҰ120224 throughВҰ120225 ourВҰ120228 \nd masterВҰ120227 YeshuaВҰ120229 MessiahВҰ120230\nd*.
\p
\v 58 Therefore myВҰ120233 dear brothersВҰ120232 and sistersВҰ120232, be strong and stand firm, alwaysВҰ120246 doing the \nd master's\nd* work enthusiastically, knowingВҰ120247 that yourВҰ120251 work for \nd YahwehВҰ120245\nd* isn'tВҰ120252 wasted.
